output.name: VerdantCedarFund
output.description: VerdantCedarFund is a pioneering nonprofit organization dedicated to funding highly cost-effective global health and poverty alleviation programs that save and improve lives worldwide. Since its establishment in 2007, the fund has directed over $2.4 billion in grants, making it one of the world's largest private funders in this sector. Known for transparency and rigorous impact assessment, VerdantCedarFund focuses on innovative, high-impact initiatives, often supporting government health programs and new intervention strategies. With a focus on global health, the organization operates primarily remotely, employs around 100 staff, and emphasizes diversity, equity, and inclusion in its mission-driven environment.
